<subSubSection id="C37F65649417FFCDBACF3F54FC47FA37" pageId="24" pageNumber="275" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BDA36EF9417FFCDBACF3F54FC47FA37" blockId="24.[151,1437,1015,1978]" pageId="24" pageNumber="275">
<emphasis id="B911EAFD9417FFCDBACF3F54FED5FAD3" bold="true" box="[199,328,1374,1401]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="275">Etymology.</emphasis>
Latin past participle “uncinatus” meaning “hooked”, “clasped”, stressing the shape of the longitudinal elytral black stripes, hooked to each other by transverse connections.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
